the starting point should be free access to the courts: r &amp; j lyons family settlement pty ltd v 155 macquarie street pty ltd [2008] nswsc 232 per bryson ja.
further, the mere fact that each proceeding is closely related is an insufficient basis to invoke the principle, given that it is concerned with substance and not form and technicalities: bazos v doman [2001] nswca 347 at [44] per stein ja (with whom priestly ja and beazley ja agreed).
i do so mindful of the fact that whether the principle applies depends on the particular circumstances involved: see egglishaw v australian crime commission (2007) 164 clr 224 and gibbs v kinna (1999) 2 vr 19 at [23] per kenny ja (with whom phillips ja agreed).